<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Triceps-Dip">Triceps Dip</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/triceps-dips" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Triceps dips</a> use a compound functional movement pattern that challenges multiple muscle groups. Because of this, tricep dips are great for developing upper body strength and power. They’re included in most <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/best-tricep-workouts" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">triceps workouts</a> for these reasons.</p>



<p>The primary movers are the triceps brachii, with all three heads being worked. Secondary movers include the abdominal heads, anterior deltoids, and upper trapezius. Triceps dips work improve pressing strength, and can be easily adapted according to your ability level.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Triceps Dips" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/964108543?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Triceps Dip Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand directly in front of a tricep dip bar. Step onto the raised platform or box and hold the parallel bars with an overhand grip. You should be facing the dip machine.</li>



<li>With your arms extended, step off the raised platform so your feet are dangling.</li>



<li>Bring your chest up and keep your head facing forward. This is the starting position.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and flex your elbows to lower your body down. Keep them tucked into your sides.</li>



<li>Pause briefly when your arms are parallel to the floor. Inhale and extend your elbows to come to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your chest up and head facing forward to target the primary movers.</li>



<li>Use a raised surface to step into the dip to maintain balance.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



